.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINYEARMONTH" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainYearMonth \- Temporal.PlainYearMonth
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[B]\f[R] object represents the
year and month of a calendar date, without a day or time zone; for
example, an event on a calendar that happens during the whole month.
It is fundamentally represented as an ISO 8601 calendar date, with year,
month, and day fields, and an associated calendar system.
The day is used to disambiguate the year\-month in non\-ISO calendar
systems.
.SH DESCRIPTION
A \f[CR]PlainYearMonth\f[R] is essentially the year\-month part of a
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object, without the day.
.SS RFC 9557 format
\f[CR]PlainYearMonth\f[R] objects can be serialized and parsed using the
\c
.UR https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc9557
RFC 9557
.UE \c
\ format, an extension to the \c
.UR https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc3339
ISO 8601 / RFC 3339
.UE \c
\ format.
The string has the following form (spaces are only for readability and
should not be present in the actual string):
.IP
.EX
YYYY\-MM\-DD [u\-ca=calendar_id]
.EE
.TP
\f[B]YYYY\f[R]
Either a four\-digit number, or a six\-digit number with a \f[CR]+\f[R]
or \f[CR]\-\f[R] sign.
.TP
\f[B]MM\f[R]
A two\-digit number from \f[CR]01\f[R] to \f[CR]12\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]DD\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A two\-digit number from \f[CR]01\f[R] to \f[CR]31\f[R].
It is required for non\-ISO calendars, and optional otherwise.
If omitted, the string looks like \f[CR]YYYY\-MM\f[R] or
\f[CR]YYYYMM\f[R].
Note that the reference day actually stored may be different from the
one you provide, but the represented year\-month is the same.
See \f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from()\f[R] for more information.
The \f[CR]YYYY\f[R], \f[CR]MM\f[R], and \f[CR]DD\f[R] components can be
separated by \f[CR]\-\f[R] or nothing.
.TP
\f[B][u\-ca=calendar_id]\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Replace \f[CR]calendar_id\f[R] with the calendar to use.
See \f[CR]Intl.supportedValuesOf()\f[R] for a list of commonly supported
calendar types.
Defaults to \f[CR][u\-ca=iso8601]\f[R].
May have a \f[I]critical flag\f[R] by prefixing the key with
\f[CR]!\f[R]: e.g., \f[CR][!u\-ca=iso8601]\f[R].
This flag generally tells other systems that it cannot be ignored if
they don\(cqt support it.
The \f[CR]Temporal\f[R] parser will throw an error if the annotations
contain two or more calendar annotations and one of them is critical.
Note that the \f[CR]YYYY\-MM\-DD\f[R] is always interpreted as an ISO
8601 calendar date and then converted to the specified calendar.
.PP
As an input, you may optionally include the time, offset, and time zone
identifier, in the same format as \f[CR]PlainDateTime\f[R], but they
will be ignored.
Other annotations in the \f[CR][key=value]\f[R] format are also ignored,
and they must not have the critical flag.
.PP
When serializing, you can configure whether to display the calendar ID,
and whether to add a critical flag for it.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth()\f[R] \f[I](experimental)\f[R]
Creates a new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] object by directly
supplying the underlying data.
.SH STATIC METHODS
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.compare()\f[R]
Returns a number (\-1, 0, or 1) indicating whether the first year\-month
comes before, is the same as, or comes after the second year\-month.
Equivalent to comparing their underlying ISO 8601 dates.
Two year\-months from different calendars may be considered equal if
they start on the same ISO date.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from()\f[R]
Creates a new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] object from another
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] object, an object with year and month
properties, or an RFC 9557 string.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
These properties are defined on
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype\f[R] and shared by all
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] instances.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.calendarId\f[R]
Returns a string representing the calendar used to interpret the
internal ISO 8601 date.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.constructor\f[R]
The constructor function that created the instance object.
For \f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] instances, the initial value is
the \f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth()\f[R] constructor.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.daysInMonth\f[R]
Returns a positive integer representing the number of days in the month
of this date.
Calendar\-dependent.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.daysInYear\f[R]
Returns a positive integer representing the number of days in the year
of this date.
Calendar\-dependent.
For the ISO 8601 calendar, this is 365, or 366 in a leap year.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.era\f[R]
Returns a calendar\-specific lowercase string representing the era of
this year\-month, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] if the calendar does not use
eras (e.g., ISO 8601).
\f[CR]era\f[R] and \f[CR]eraYear\f[R] together uniquely identify a year
in a calendar, in the same way that \f[CR]year\f[R] does.
Calendar\-dependent.
For Gregorian, it is either \f[CR]\(dqgregory\(dq\f[R] or
\f[CR]\(dqgregory\-inverse\(dq\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.eraYear\f[R]
Returns a non\-negative integer representing the year of this
year\-month within the era, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] if the calendar does
not use eras (e.g., ISO 8601).
The year index usually starts from 1 (more common) or 0, and years in an
era can decrease with time (e.g., Gregorian BCE).
\f[CR]era\f[R] and \f[CR]eraYear\f[R] together uniquely identify a year
in a calendar, in the same way that \f[CR]year\f[R] does.
Calendar\-dependent.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.inLeapYear\f[R]
Returns a boolean indicating whether this year\-month is in a leap year.
A leap year is a year that has more days (due to a leap day or leap
month) than a common year.
Calendar\-dependent.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.month\f[R]
Returns a positive integer representing the 1\-based month index in the
year of this year\-month.
The first month of this year is \f[CR]1\f[R], and the last month is the
\f[CR]monthsInYear\f[R].
Calendar\-dependent.
Note that unlike \f[CR]Date.prototype.getMonth()\f[R], the index is
1\-based.
If the calendar has leap months, then the month with the same
\f[CR]monthCode\f[R] may have different \f[CR]month\f[R] indexes for
different years.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.monthCode\f[R]
Returns a calendar\-specific string representing the month of this
year\-month.
Calendar\-dependent.
Usually it is \f[CR]M\f[R] plus a two\-digit month number.
For leap months, it is the previous month\(cqs code followed by
\f[CR]L\f[R].
If the leap month is the first month of the year, the code is
\f[CR]M00L\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.monthsInYear\f[R]
Returns a positive integer representing the number of months in the year
of this date.
Calendar\-dependent.
For the ISO 8601 calendar, this is always 12, but in other calendar
systems it may differ.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.year\f[R]
Returns an integer representing the number of years of this year\-month
relative to the start of a calendar\-specific epoch year.
Calendar\-dependent.
Usually year 1 is either the first year of the latest era or the ISO
8601 year \f[CR]0001\f[R].
If the epoch is in the middle of the year, that year will have the same
value before and after the start date of the era.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype[Symbol.toStringTag]\f[R]
The initial value of the \f[CR][Symbol.toStringTag]\f[R] property is the
string \f[CR]\(dqTemporal.PlainYearMonth\(dq\f[R].
This property is used in \f[CR]Object.prototype.toString()\f[R].
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.add()\f[R]
Returns a new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] object representing
this year\-month moved forward by a given duration (in a form
convertible by \f[CR]Temporal.Duration.from()\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.equals()\f[R]
Returns \f[CR]true\f[R] if this year\-month is equivalent in value to
another year\-month (in a form convertible by
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from()\f[R]), and \f[CR]false\f[R]
otherwise.
They are compared both by their underlying ISO date values and their
calendars, so two year\-months from different calendars may be
considered equal by \f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.compare()\f[R] but not
by \f[CR]equals()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.since()\f[R]
Returns a new \f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] object representing the
duration from another year\-month (in a form convertible by
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from()\f[R]) to this year\-month.
The duration is positive if the other month is before this month, and
negative if after.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.subtract()\f[R]
Returns a new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] object representing
this year\-month moved backward by a given duration (in a form
convertible by \f[CR]Temporal.Duration.from()\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.toJSON()\f[R]
Returns a string representing this year\-month in the same RFC 9557
format as calling \f[CR]toString()\f[R].
Intended to be implicitly called by \f[CR]JSON.stringify()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.toLocaleString()\f[R]
Returns a string with a language\-sensitive representation of this
year\-month.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.toPlainDate()\f[R]
Returns a new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object representing this
year\-month and a supplied day in the same calendar system.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.toString()\f[R]
Returns a string representing this year\-month in the RFC 9557 format.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.until()\f[R]
Returns a new \f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] object representing the
duration from this year\-month to another year\-month (in a form
convertible by \f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from()\f[R]).
The duration is positive if the other month is after this month, and
negative if before.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.valueOf()\f[R]
Throws a \f[CR]TypeError\f[R], which prevents
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] instances from being implicitly
converted to primitives when used in arithmetic or comparison
operations.
.TP
\f[B]Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.with()\f[R]
Returns a new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] object representing
this year\-month with some fields replaced by new values.
